    {
      "_id": "7c3Fruapop9Ds7DU",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
      "name": "Engulfing Mists",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>@Check[type:fortitude|dc:28], [[/r {2d6}[negative damage]]]{2d6 negative damage}</p>\n<p>A creature engulfed by a trench mist does not gain the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Grabbed]{Grabbed} or slowed conditions-such a creature is not in danger of suffocating, but as long as it begins its turn engulfed, the trench mist may make misty tendrils Strikes against the engulfed creature. An engulfed creature does not need to make an @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Escape]{Escape} check to exit the engulf. All engulfed creatures become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Concealed]{Concealed}, and all creatures outside the mist become concealed to creatures within it.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>@Localize[PF2E.NPC.Abilities.Glossary.Engulf]</p>"
        },
